race.comment: The $200,000 Group 3 George Moore Stakes. CABALLUS (1) didn't measure up in Group 1 company last time out but will find this assignment much more to his liking. Ready to peak now fourth run back from the break and hails from an in-form yard. Should be in this for a long way. HIDDEN WEALTH (2) is two from three around this circuit and is drawn to get all the favours from the inside alley. Has to be included. TAVS (5) has put back-to-back wins together and has hit a purple patch of form of late. Cannot be discounted lightly. The well-related PEREILLE (9) (full to G2 winner Corniche) is a very consistent conveyance who is usually thereabouts. One for the exotics. EPIC PROPORTIONS (10) is a last-start winner who shouldn't be slept on.
